You can do this with a one-liner using **Instancio**:

```java
Person person = Instancio.create(Person.class);
```

This returns a populated person including nested objects and collections. You can also use the builder API to customise generated values:

```java
Person person = Instancio.of(Person.class)
    .generate(field(&quot;age&quot;), gen -&gt; gen.ints().range(18, 65))
    .create();
```

If you use JUnit 5, you can also use it with `@ParameterizedTest`s:

```java
@ExtendWith(InstancioExtension.class)
