The problem is

&gt; When a Scanner is closed, it will close its input source if the source implements the Closeable interface.

http://docs.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/util/Scanner.html

Thus `scan.close()` closes `System.in`.


To fix it you can make

`Scanner scan` `static`
and do not close it in PromptCustomerQty.  Code below works.


